Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
refine_macro_place(25.10)                            refine_macro_place(25.10)

Name
       refine_macro_place  - Legalizes the macros based on constraints such as
       halo and blockages, forbidden spacing, min-space, etc

Syntax
        refine_macro_place

       [-help]

       [-verbose ]

       Legalizes the macros based on constraints such as halo  and  blockages,
       forbidden spacing, min-space, etc. To define the constraints of macros,
       use the set_macro_place_constraint command.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each refine_macro_place  parameter.  For  a  de-
              tailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use
              the man command:

              man refine_macro_place

       -verbose
              Writes the macro movement details to a tcl file.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Example
       The following command specifies the minimum space between macro-to-core
       boundary as 5 and the forbidden space between macro-to-core boundary as
       2.

       set_macro_place_constraint          -forbidden_space_to_core          2
       -min_space_to_core 5

       refine_macro_place

Related Information
              * set_macro_place_constraint

              * setPlaceMode

              * Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

              * Using the Mixed Placer chapter in the Innovus User Guide

